    "answer_id" : 2728515,
    "question_id" : 2728495,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<blockquote>\n  <p>RMI or Remote Method Invokation is\n  very similar to RPC or Remote\n  Procedure call in that the client\n  both send proxy objects (or stubs) to\n  the server however the subtle\n  difference is that client side RPC\n  invokes <strong>FUNCTIONS</strong> through the proxy\n  function and RMI invokes <strong>METHODS</strong>\n  through the proxy function. <strong>RMI is\n  considered slightly superior as it is\n  an object-oriented</strong> version of RPC.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>From <a href=\"http://wiki.answers.com/Q/Difference_between_RMI_and_RPC\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n\n<p>For more information and examples, have a <a href=\"http://wiki.answers.com/Q/What_is_RPC_and_RMI_Give_appropriates_examples\" rel=\"noreferrer\">look here</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
